<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-26T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-26T19:00:00-05:00" n="1012" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1012">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9327/5–2749: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The Minister-Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Clark</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canton</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_apparent-typo-based-on-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-27T08:00:00+08:00">May 27, 1949—8
                                a. m.</date>
                            <lb/> [Received May 27—5:28 a. m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Cantel 483. Foreign Office confirmed today renewal Sino-Soviet air pact
                        unchanged for 5 years, Cantel 452, May 23, repeated Nanking 315, Shanghai
                        268.</p>
                    <p>Sent Department Cantel 483, repeated Nanking 331, Shanghai 286.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Clark</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>